    <div class="content">
        <h1>A Spatial Analysis By Louis Drulhe</h1>

        <h2>Background Info</h2>

        <p>
            The purpose of the atlas is to use spatial analysis as a key to understanding social, political, and economic issues on the Internet.
        </p>

        <h3>Quotes</h3>

        <ul class="quote-list">
            <li>"The strength of the Internet is a concentration of power in a single point incorporating the whole world."</li>
            <li>"On the Internet, distance has no relevance, but the notion of space nevertheless remains."</li>
            <li>"The Internet we use is actually a projection of itself through the prism of locality. Internet is a single entity, but with a myriad of territorial projections."</li>
            <li>"Instead of being distributed over several different points, the weight of the Internet is concentrated solely at one focal point."</li>
            <li>"The Internet exists physically and occupies an inconspicuous space on Earth."</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Responses</h3>

        <p>
          The quotes on the spatial analysis of the Internet offer intriguing perspectives on the complex relationship between the digital realm and physical space. "The strength of the Internet is a concentration of power in a single point incorporating the whole world" highlights the immense influence wielded by central hubs in our interconnected world. Despite the absence of physical distance online, "On the Internet, distance has no relevance, but the notion of space nevertheless remains" reminds us that a virtual geography emerges, defined by the spaces we navigate and the communities we engage with. "The Internet we use is actually a projection of itself through the prism of locality" underscores the idea that the Internet's global nature emerges from countless local interactions and manifestations. "Instead of being distributed over several different points, the weight of the Internet is concentrated solely at one focal point" suggests the pivotal role played by key nodes in sustaining the digital ecosystem. Lastly, "The Internet exists physically and occupies an inconspicuous space on Earth" prompts us to recognize that beneath its intangible veneer, the Internet is grounded in tangible infrastructure, subtly woven into the fabric of our physical world. These quotes collectively emphasize the duality of the Internet, which simultaneously transcends and reflects our physical reality.

        </p>
        <h6>By Yingchen Zheng</h6>
